<h3 id='sale-updates'>Sale Updates</h3><pre class="highlight php tab-php"><code><span class="cp">&lt;?php</span>

<span class="k">use</span> <span class="nx">Inspetor</span><span class="p">;</span>

<span class="nv">$inspetor</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nv">$this</span><span class="o">-&gt;</span><span class="na">getConfiguredInspetor</span><span class="p">();</span>

<span class="nv">$inspetor</span><span class="o">-&gt;</span><span class="na">trackSaleUpdate</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nv">$sale</span><span class="p">);</span>

<span class="cp">?&gt;</span>
</code></pre>
<p>Send information to Inspetor every time a sale&#39;s status is updated.
<aside class="notice">
You must call this function <b>any</b> time a sale&#39;s status is updated (including post-sale updates, such as refunds). Sale status is extremely crucial to Inspetor&#39;s prediction model.
</aside></p>

<table><thead>
<tr>
<th>Argument</th>
<th>Type</th>
<th>Description</th>
</tr>
</thead><tbody>
<tr>
<td>sale</td>
<td>Inspetor/Model/<a href="#inspetorsale">InspetorSale</a></td>
<td>The Sale that is being updated</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
